<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The memcmp call reads 5 bytes from hdr->value unconditionally. If response->flags_auto has MHD_RAF_HAS_CONNECTION_HDR set but hdr is NULL (MHD_get_response_element_n_ returned NULL) or hdr->value points to a buffer shorter than 5 bytes (e.g. header value "clo" or an empty value), memcmp(hdr->value, "close", 5) will access bytes beyond the object bounds (undefined behavior). There is no prior check that hdr != NULL or that hdr->value_size >= 5, so out‑of‑bounds access is possible.
</scenario>

